# Keep the monorepo build context lean (used by the repo-root Docker builds).
**/node_modules
**/.next
**/dist
**/build
**/.turbo
**/coverage
**/.terraform
**/*.tfstate*
.git
.github
**/*.log
**/.env
**/.env.local
**/.env.*.local
# Frontend is excluded from the lean backend build contexts, EXCEPT the two frontends built
# from the repo root: auth-baalvion (core-auth-baalvion) and admin-platform (admin-web, the
# admin.baalvion.com console). Re-include just those; their build artifacts stay excluded by
# the **/node_modules etc. rules below. NOTE: without admin-platform here, its source never
# enters the build context and `turbo prune baalvion-admin-platform` fails "package not found".
Frontend/*
!Frontend/auth-baalvion
!Frontend/admin-platform
Frontend/auth-baalvion/node_modules
Frontend/auth-baalvion/.next
Frontend/auth-baalvion/.turbo
Frontend/admin-platform/node_modules
Frontend/admin-platform/.next
Frontend/admin-platform/.turbo
e2e
docs
*.md
